              <table class="table">
              <tr><td>
                <h1 class="white-text">LANGUAGE OF CHESS üèÅ</h1>
              </td></tr>
              <tr><td>
              <p class="white-text">Every square in chess has a name based on a coordinate system. All files have a letter, from a - h, going from the queen's rook file to the king's rook file. Each rank has a number from the 1st and 2nd rank where White's pieces begin through the 7th and 8th rank where Black's pieces begin. Each piece is notated this way:

King = K.
Queen = Q.
Rook = R.
Bishop = B.
Knight = N.
Pawn - no symbol.

You write a move with the letter of the piece followed by the letter and numbers of the square. For example, Kf3 if a king reaches the f3 square, or if you place a pawn on f3 then just f3 because pawns have no symbol. </p>
              </td></tr>
              </table>
            </td>
