                <h1 class="white-text">CHECK üèÅ</h1>
              </td></tr>
              <tr><td>
              <p class="white-text">Check means that one side is threatening to capture the opposing king. You never capture the king in chess, so the other side must get out of check. 

To notate a check, you add a "+" to the end of your notation. For example, knight to g6 with a check is notated as Ng6+.. </p>
              </td></tr>
              </table>
            </td>
